<h1>Disputed Dungeons: Fighting anti-D&amp;D falsehoods</h1>
<p class="subtitle">From <a href="http://www.jonnydigital.com/">Jonathan's Reference Pages</a></p>
<hr><!-- ======================================================== -->

<p>In 1982, a young Tom Hanks starred in <cite>Mazes and Monsters</cite>,
a movie about a young man who loses his mind after playing a fantasy
roleplaying game. Incredibly, many audiences took this film seriously,
and it sparked a worldwide backlash against the <cite>Dungeons &amp;
Dragons</cite> that seriously damaged the game's reputation.</p>

<p>What follows are a list of refutations of articles, publications
or arguments that have been used to mislead, and continue to do so.</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="dark-dungeons">Dark Dungeons: Jack Chick's misleading propaganda</a></li>
  <li><a href="straight-talk-on-dungeons-and-dragons">Straight Talk on Dungeons and Dragons</a></li>
  <li><a href="dungeons-and-dragons-controversy-links">Dungeons &amp; Dragons controversy links</a></li>
</ul>

